example : traversing 1->0->1 :-
when we start with 1(1 is root), then value 1 to binary is 2^0 * 1 === 1,
when we traverses to 1->0 (from 1 to 0), then it is 2^1 * 1 + 2^0 * 0 == 2   note : the previous node value just get doubled and we just the current node since 2's power 0 is 1 only, so 1*2 + 1 * 0 = 2
when we traverses to 1->0->1, then ->  2 * (value of 1->0) + 1 = (2 * 2 )+ 1
so 1->0->1 = 5
