# Solution
Calculate the number top-to-bottom, stop at the leaf and return the result.

Sum results for all leaves; make sure we handle parents with only one child (return 0 for the missing child).
```
int sumRootToLeaf(TreeNode* r, int val = 0) {
  if (r == nullptr) return 0;
  val = ((val << 1) + r->val) % 1000000007;
  return (r->left == r->right ? val : sumRootToLeaf(r->left, val) + sumRootToLeaf(r->right, val)) % 1000000007;
}
```
# Complexity Analysis
Runtime: *O(n)*; we process each node once. 
Memory: *O(h)*, where *h* is the height of the tree.

