This is a typical tree traversal problem. Both DFS and BFS should work in this setting. The only trick is that one needs to keep track of the value (binary value) up to the node that is being traversed. Below is a iterative implementation of DFS. 
```
class Solution:
    def sumRootToLeaf(self, root: Optional[TreeNode]) -> int:
        ans = 0 
        stack = [(root, 0)]
        while stack: 
            node, val = stack.pop()
            val = 2*val + node.val 
            if node.left is node.right: ans += val 
            if node.left: stack.append((node.left, val))
            if node.right: stack.append((node.right, val))
        return ans 
```

