solutions.content:
The max number of days we can wait is  = maximum value of days required to bloom flower in given input. 
While minimum days = minimum value required to bloom flower. 
Our task is to find the minimum number of days so that we have sufficient flowers to form required bouquets.

So, We do binary search from 0 to max to find the minimum number of days that gives sufficient m group of k consecutive flowers.

```csharp
public int MinDays(int[] bloomDay, int m, int k)
{
	int flowersRequired = m * k;
	int flowersAvailable = bloomDay.Length;

	if (flowersAvailable < flowersRequired)
	{
		return -1;
	}

	int min = int.MaxValue;
	int max = int.MinValue;
	foreach(var flower in bloomDay)
	{
		min = Math.Min(min, flower);
		max = Math.Max(max, flower);
	}

	int low = min;
	int high = max;

	while (low < high)
	{
		int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;

		int currentBlooomed = 0;
		int bouquets = 0;

		foreach (var flower in bloomDay)
		{
			if (flower <= mid)
			{
				currentBlooomed++;
			}
			else
			{
				currentBlooomed = 0;
			}

			if (currentBlooomed == k)
			{
				currentBlooomed = 0;
				bouquets++;
			}
		}

		if (bouquets >= m)
		{
			high = mid;
		}
		else
		{
			low = mid + 1;
		}
	}

	return low;
}
```

