This solution was a little tricky, not in thought but in implementation, I figured out the binary search approach in 5 mins, the check function took a few fails to understand properly (even though that part was basically heavily hinted by question description examples).

For those who don't understand a binary search problem easily, they usually involve a continuous range you have to check and this range does not necessarily consist of the input array and the solution demands min or max in that range where the solution changes from false to true or vice versa.

Questions that are similar and will help get this idea down:
#### EASY: 
* [First Bad Version](https://leetcode.com/problems/first-bad-version/) | **Same template you don't have to write condition yourself**
#### MEDIUM: 
