**Approach:-** Applying Binary Search on Answer Approach.
-->What Actully we are doing?

-->**The Lowest Day we require** = Minimum Element of array.
-->**The Highest Day we require is** = Maximum Element of array.

Now We Check In Between thease days:-
**We Calculate a mid day.:-**
And For Mid day we check how many Bouquets we will form by taking consecutive **k** flowers(whithin mid day)

-->If the total number of Bouquets form within mid day is greater than equal to **m**
  -->Then this is our one of the Possible answer. so we update high=mid-1; 

-->If the total number of boquet form within mid day is less than m.
then we increase low=mid+1;


To understand what is happening inside **isPossible** function look at the code and read comment.
```
class Solution {
public: 
    bool isPossible(vector<int>&nums,int mid,int k,int m)
    {
        /*Its Little bit Sliding window type.
        But not same*/
        int i=0,n=nums.size(),count=0;

        while(i+k-1<n) //For Every window of k from starting from any index i.
        {
            int mx=INT_MIN;
            int index=-1;
            for(int j=i;j<=i+k-1;j++) //For that window we will find maximimum element and its index.
            {
                if(nums[j]>=mx)
                    mx=nums[j],index=j;
            }
            if(mx>mid) //for that window if mx>mid, means it is not Possible to form boquest withim mid days.
                i=index+1; //So we increase our i to index+1.
            else
            {
                i=i+k; //i=i+k means ,this window is ok ,search for wIndOw after that window.
                count++; //Increase the Count
            }
        }

        return count>=m?1:0; //If count is greater than m means it is possible ans.
    }
    int minDays(vector<int>& nums, int m, int k) {
        int low=*min_element(nums.begin(),nums.end()); //Lowest days we require,
        int high=*max_element(nums.begin(),nums.end()); //Highest days we require

        int ans=-1;

        while(low<=high)
        {
            int mid=low+(high-low)/2;

            if(isPossible(nums,mid,k,m))
            {
                ans=mid;
                high=mid-1;
            }
            else
                low=mid+1;
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```
