## Complexity
- Time complexity:
$O(n * 26)$ -> To calculate largest color value using BFS
$O(n)$ -> To detect cycle using DFS
**Overall Time Complexity** = $O(n*26) + O(n) \approx O(n)$

- Space complexity:
$O(n * 26)$ -> To store the largest color value at each node
$O(3 * n)$ -> To detect cycle using DFS
**Overall Time Complexity** = $O(n*26) + O(3 * n) \approx O(n)$

## First Approach
First thing we all can identify that if there is a cycle then we have to return -1.
And the second thing if we visit a node(current node) from a parent node then we have to copy all the color value from parent node and increase the current node's colour value by 1.

And in every step we update the maxcolor variable according to maximum color value.

At last return the maxcolor.

# code
```
class Solution {
    bool detectCycle(int s, vector<vector<int>>& adj, vector<int>& vis, vector<int>& pathVis)
    {
        if(!vis[s]) {
            vis[s] = 1;
            pathVis[s] = 1;

            for(int x : adj[s]) {
                if(detectCycle(x, adj, vis, pathVis)) {
                    return true;
                }
            }
            pathVis[s] = 0;
        } else if(pathVis[s]) {
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
public:
    int largestPathValue(string colors, vector<vector<int>>& edges)
    {
        int maxcolor = -1;
        vector<vector<int>> adj(colors.size());

        for(auto x : edges) {
            adj[x[0]].push_back(x[1]);
        }

        vector<int> vis(adj.size());
        vector<int> pathVis(adj.size());
        if(detectCycle(0, adj, vis, pathVis)) {
            return -1;
        }
        vector<vector<int>> dp(adj.size(), vector<int>(26, 0));

        for(int i = 0; i < adj.size(); i++) {

            //When we visit a node we increase its color value by 1;
            dp[i][colors[i] - 97] += 1;

            /*we increase the color value in this stage only so we
            may get the maxcolor value only in this stage*/
            maxcolor = max(maxcolor, dp[i][colors[i] - 97]);
            for(int x : adj[i]) {
                for(int col = 0; col < 26; col++) {
                    if(dp[x][col] < dp[i][col]) {
                        dp[x][col] = dp[i][col]; 
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return maxcolor;
    }
};
```
## Above code will fail for the following test case
"bbbhb"
[[0,2],[3,0],[1,3],[4,1]]

For the above test case we vist from 0 to 2 then we visit 1 to 3 and then 3 to 0. To get max value we have to again vist node 2 to 0.
For very long test cases if we visit again a visited node then we will get **TLE**.
To avoid it we have to visit the graph(adjacency list) in topological order.
The topological order of the above test case is:
    1->3->0->2

## Modifiaction of First Approach
we have to sort the graph node in topological order.
To do the above we store the node(which we visit first) in a vector(at last).
Here we perform the above task inside dectcycle function(visiting the graph node using DFS). 

# Final Code
```
