DP approach to store count of colors for each node:
We slightly modify the topo sort algo to store count of color.
At each node we store cnt[node][26] where cnt[node][i] is the maximum frequency count of color i seen in all paths that end on current node.

For example, assume there are two paths reaching the current node- abaca, aaabba. Then cnt['a'] = 4, cnt['b'] = 2 and cnt['c'] = 1.
Count of 'a' is 4 because the max appearance of color 'a' is in 2nd path where it  appears 4 times.  Similarly count 'b' is 2 as it appears twice in 2nd path and count 'c' is 1 as it appears only once in path 1.
Answer will be the max value seen in cnt[] of any node.

C++ solution:
```
class Solution {
public:
    int largestPathValue(string colors, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        int n = colors.length();
        vector<int> in(n, 0);
        vector<vector<int>> g(n);
        int cnt[n][26];
        memset(cnt, 0, sizeof cnt);
        int ans = 0; 

        // Make adj list graph.
        for(auto &edge: edges){
            g[edge[0]].push_back(edge[1]);
            in[edge[1]]++;
        }

        // Push the vertices with 0 indegree to queue.
        queue<int> q;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(!in[i])
                q.push(i);
        }

        // Topological sort.
        while(!q.empty()){
            int node = q.front(); q.pop();
            int col = colors[node]-'a';
            cnt[node][col]++;                 // Increment the count of color at current node.
            ans = max(ans, cnt[node][col]);    // Update answer to max value count value.
            for(auto &child: g[node]){
                for(int i=0; i<26; i++){    
                    cnt[child][i] = max(cnt[child][i], cnt[node][i]);     // Inherit max count value in child node from parent node.
                }
                in[child]--;                       // Remove the incoming edge by decrementing the indegree of child node.
                if(!in[child])                     // Enqueue child node in queue if it's indegree becomes 0.
                    q.push(child);
            }
        }

        // Check for cycle in graph.
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++)
            if(in[i])
                return -1;

        return ans;
    }
};
```
Time Complexity: O(V+E)
Space Complexity: O(V+E)

